<b>Carnatic Music</b>
<br>

<p>I am an ardent lover of carnatic classical music and a singer too. 

I was learning music under the tutelage of  Padmashri Palghat Sri.

<a href="kvnbio.html">K.

V. Narayanaswamy</a>,<a href="kvnolder.jpg">

(picture)

</a>who's my  and many music lover's favourite artist. I

was very fortunate to had him as a Guru, for he is so versatile not only

in singing but also in teaching.</p>

<p>I started my basic music lessons from Mrs. Visalakshi

and continued it under Sri. T. K. Subramaniam in Tirunelveli (south India) until I came

over to Madras for joining the masters in IIT. I have 15+ years of music training.

<p>My favourite classical singers include M. D. Ramanathan, Madurai Sri.

Mani Iyer, Madurai Sri. T. N. Seshagopalan. If I have to mention the favourite of mine it is MDR and next comes KVN

<p>Here is my<a href="http://www.narada.org"> Guru's homepage

</a>which

has some old evergreen concerts.  

<br> 

<p>Here is a sample of my voice. It is a wounderful piece - Ennamum orutharam in the raga Yadukula Kambhoji in adi tata composed by Gopalakrishna Bharathi

<br>

